Class GraphDifferencingIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.common.collect.UnmodifiableIterator<T>
      • com.google.common.collect.AbstractIterator<com.hp.hpl.jena.graph.Triple>
        • org.fcrepo.kernel.utils.iterators.GraphDifferencingIterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterator<com.hp.hpl.jena.graph.Triple>

    public class GraphDifferencingIterator
extends com.google.common.collect.AbstractIterator<com.hp.hpl.jena.graph.Triple>
    A wrapping Iterator that calculates two differences between a Graph A and a source Iterator B. The differences are (A - (A ∩ B)) and (B - (A ∩ B)). The ordinary output of this iterator is (B - (A ∩ B)), and after exhaustion, sets containing (A - (A ∩ B)) and (A ∩ B) are available.
    Since:
    Oct 24, 2013
    Author:
    ajs6f
